<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14186">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Woodwork.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9800">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9800 mb-requirement-id-9801">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in woodwork activities, and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards.
        Explain what precautions you should take to safely use your tools.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/GQkUbdE3VS8?si=EpcwqUnpU9BDS6Cz"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety in Woodworking | Woodworking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9800 mb-requirement-id-9802">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries that could occur while
        woodworking, including splinters, scratches, cuts, severe bleeding, and
        shock. Tell what precautions must be taken to help prevent loss of
        eyesight or hearing, and explain why and when it is necessary to use a
        dust mask. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/A0EmfREhgRw?si=fh9F6uKkRvb4ogza"
          target="_blank"
          >The Emergency First Aid Kit for Woodworkers Need! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9800 mb-requirement-id-9803">
        (c) Earn the Totin' Chip recognition.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9804">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9804 mb-requirement-id-9805">
        (a) Describe how timber is grown, harvested, and milled. Tell how lumber
        is cured, seasoned, graded, and sized. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hOO37pcFg5I?si=K7r13Z-hpu-ZMAxB"
          target="_blank"
          >How Trees Are Made Into Lumber (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9804 mb-requirement-id-9806">
        (b) Collect and label blocks of six kinds of wood useful in woodworking.
        Describe the chief qualities of each. Give the best uses of each.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9807">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9807 mb-requirement-id-9808">
        (a) Show the proper care, use, and storage of all working tools and
        equipment that you own or use at home or school. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://deltamachinery.com/tool-maintenance-101-tips-for-keepingyour-woodworking-tools-in-top-condition/"
          target="_blank"
          >Tool Maintenance 101: Tips for KeepingYour Woodworking Tools in Top
          Condition (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9807 mb-requirement-id-9809">
        (b) Sharpen correctly the cutting edges of two different tools. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2mJZH29bAHI?si=EdoNp283FRVbkTp_"
          target="_blank"
          >Best Method for Sharpening Your Chisels and Plane Irons (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9816">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Using a saw, plane, hammer, brace, and bit, make something useful of wood.
      Cut parts from lumber that you have squared and measured from working
      drawings. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/xV6ql13lfjw?si=02XiV7e925ictjOt" target="_blank"
        >Build This Simple Wooden Tool Box - Hand Saw And A Hammer (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/3WIjpz9Ut1c?si=ngE7zV5uIDXLN10w" target="_blank"
        >How to Make a Bench Hook (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9817">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Create your own woodworking project. Begin by making working drawings,
      list the materials you will need to complete your project, and then build
      your project. Keep track of the time you spend and the cost of the
      materials.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9810">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9810 mb-requirement-id-9811">
        (a) Make working drawings of a project needing beveled or rounded edges
        and build it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/l06lCTcOgHQ?si=zFKD2q75qtORQzr"
          target="_blank"
          >Bevels- How to Make Beveled Panels on the Tablesaw (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/XztV4yjfFaI?si=8y6bA5TuRF-Tmoyv"
          target="_blank"
          >Rounded Edges- How to Rout Round Corners (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9810 mb-requirement-id-9812">
        (b) Make working drawings of a project needing curved or incised
        cuttings and build it. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/867ho1Pp12U?si=T3zGA7JYZkWODfDv"
          target="_blank"
          >Making Arcs &amp; Curves the Easy Way (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9810 mb-requirement-id-9813">
        (c) Make working drawings of a project needing miter, dowel, or mortise
        and tenon joints and build it. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/h0ryuL0DuLE?si=aq-2Jk5UxvEdtZ4F"
          target="_blank"
          >Mitered Mortise &amp; Tenon Joint (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9810 mb-requirement-id-9814">
        (d) Make a cabinet, box, or something else with a door or lid fastened
        with inset hinges. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Syv3JzRXld8?si=LG_MXwk4-tBuDBgK"
          target="_blank"
          >The Special Wooden Box / Invisible Wooden Hinge - Using Basic Tools /
          Dovetail Joints (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TazBJ5MSMgc?si=ulffNFnBiQ-I22fi"
          target="_blank"
          >An Absurd Number of Wood Box Making Tips &amp; Tricks (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9810 mb-requirement-id-9815">
        (e) Help make wooden toys for underprivileged children; OR help carry
        out a woodworking service project approved by your counselor for a
        charitable organization. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IwLwNGAxSfg?si=upaHucGcY9scLFYB"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Make Wooden Toys for Kids | DIY | Great Home Ideas (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9818">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Talk with a cabinetmaker or finish carpenter. Learn about training,
      apprenticeships, career opportunities, work conditions, work hours, pay
      rates, and union organization that woodworking experts have in your area.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/lPTR2xdIz9M?si=pyFe8tLbhOh0zqT3" target="_blank"
        >A Day @ AWC : Careers in the Wood Industry (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/NBHhOMEs9Sk?si=JNOrbPzgNwLd6TK9" target="_blank"
        >Kayleen McCabe - Her Career in Woodworking (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/zCNgrOR8FEU?si=U9HEuwvA3fi3iqOn" target="_blank"
        >A Total Beginner's Guide to Woodworking (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
